The High Court of England and Wales grants the Attorney General permission to bring a case against The Sun and the Daily Mirror for the way they reported aspects of the hunt for the killer of Joanna Yeates. (BBC)It is revealed that police have contacted the parents of murdered schoolgirls Holly Wells and Jessica Chapman amid concerns that the News of the World tabloid also hacked them. (The Guardian) (Channel 4 News) (BBC) (The Belfast Telegraph)